### Tracker + recent runs (each row in BatchMetrics joins back via runId)
GET http://localhost:4106/pipeline/Pipelines?$filter=name eq 'Shipments'&$expand=runs($orderby=startTime desc;$top=5)

### Status
GET http://localhost:4106/pipeline/status(name='Shipments')

### Flush — resets tracker + clears the local table (BatchMetrics is a
### separate table and survives flushes by design).
POST http://localhost:4106/pipeline/flush
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments"}
